article.headline: Yale 72, Dartmouth 55
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Eric Flato hit back-to-back three-pointers during a 14-4 run midway through the second half that propelled Yale to a 72-55 win Saturday over Dartmouth in the Ivy League. Senior center Dominick Martin led Yale with 15 points and junior forward Sam Kaplan made four of five field and finished with 13 points. Flato, Caleb Homes and Casey Hughes all had eight. Hughes added seven rebounds and three assists for Yale (11-8, 3-1 Ivy). Dartmouth (2-15, 0-4 Ivy) was led by Dan Biber's career-high 16 points. The Big Green, which trailed 30-22 at the half, pulled to within 45-41 on a Jonathan Ball lay-up with 11:11 left before Yale went on its run. Yale shot 60 percent from the floor in the second half and 55.8 percent for the game. The Bulldogs used an 11-0 run in the first half to build a 23-11 lead on a Kaplan jumper with 7:09 left. Yale held Dartmouth to 35.6 percent shooting, the fifth straight game an opponent has not shot better than 40 percent. The Bulldogs have won 10 of the past 11 against Dartmouth.
